-- U.S.'s Isner Beats Mahut at Wimbledon in Longest Match in Sport of Tennis
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-24T15:49:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/u-s-s-isner-beats-mahut-at-wimbledon-in-longest-match-in-sport-of-tennis.html

          
          
             John Isner of the U.S. beat Franceâ€™s
Nicolas Mahut in the first-round of Wimbledon in the longest
match in tennis history.  
 The No. 23 seed won 6-4, 3-6, 6-7 (7-9), 7-6 (7-3), 70-68.  
 Before today, the longest match had been a six hour, 33
minute first round match at the 2004 French Open between
Frenchmen Fabrice Santoro and Arnaud Clement.  
          
          


  


        